intro: Uragoga bidentata, commonly known as the two-toothed uragoga, is a flowering plant native to parts of Southeast Asia. It belongs to the family Araliaceae and is characterized by its compound leaves with two distinct teeth on each leaflet. The plant produces small, greenish-white flowers that are clustered in umbels, typical of the family. Uragoga bidentata is often found in moist, shaded forest environments. Its botanical features make it an interesting subject for ecological and taxonomic studies.
